  "prompt": "What is the meaning of the ratios written on RC toys eg.1:14, 1:24?",
  "response": "The ratios written on RC (remote control) toys, such as 1:14 or 1:24, refer to the **scale** of the model compared to the real-life version of the object it represents. \n\n- **1:14** means that the RC toy is 1/14th the size of the actual object.  \n- **1:24** means that the RC toy is 1/24th the size of the actual object.\n\nFor example, if you have a 1:14 scale RC car of a vehicle that is 14 feet long in real life, the RC model would be 1 foot long. Similarly, a 1:24 scale model of the same 14-foot vehicle would be about 7 inches long.\n\nThese ratios help enthusiasts understand how large or small the RC model is relative to the real thing and are often used to compare different models.",
